00:00:52,469 --> 00:00:55,597
Don't forget we can't afford
to lose a single match now.

24
00:00:55,597 --> 00:00:57,808
That's enough
motivation for me.

25
00:00:57,808 --> 00:01:01,019
It's time we showed them
how good Aibo really is.

26
00:01:01,019 --> 00:01:03,230
Come on, guys,
it's go time!

27
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:04,523
Yeah, right on.

28
00:01:04,523 --> 00:02:35,989
♪

29
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:45,624
Zanya's in the
spotlight again!

30
00:02:45,624 --> 00:02:46,458
A girl!

31
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:47,501
People are
dying to know.

32
00:02:47,501 --> 00:02:48,835
How are
you feeling?

33
00:02:48,835 --> 00:02:51,004
Well, I know
I'm gonna win.

34
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:54,633
As for my feelings,
I, uh, Akatsuki!

35
00:02:54,633 --> 00:02:56,968
If you're looking
for your little bro,

36
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:59,805
last I saw him, he was dancing
around kinda like this.

37
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:01,807
Huh?

38
00:03:01,807 --> 00:03:04,643
Yeah, that can
only mean one thing.

39
00:03:04,643 --> 00:03:06,061
What did I tell ya?

40
00:03:06,061 --> 00:03:08,230
These humans are
seriously weird.

41
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:10,774
♪

42
00:03:10,774 --> 00:03:14,361
(whimpering)

43
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:17,614
Come on, why don't
(indistinct whining)

44
00:03:17,614 --> 00:03:24,621
♪

45
00:03:24,621 --> 00:03:29,000
Whew.

46
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,169
Ow! Hey, what's the deal?

47
00:03:31,169 --> 00:03:32,045
Huh?

48
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:33,088
(screams)

49
00:03:33,088 --> 00:03:35,215
Intruder detected.

50
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:36,425
What's he doing?

51
00:03:36,425 --> 00:03:38,510
The match is starting
any second now.

52
00:03:38,510 --> 00:03:41,096
Hey!

53
00:03:41,096 --> 00:03:43,140
Does this belong to you?

54
00:03:43,140 --> 00:03:44,599
Let him go!

55
00:03:44,599 --> 00:03:48,019
♪

56
00:03:48,019 --> 00:03:51,231
Sending the runt
over to spy on us, huh?

57
00:03:51,231 --> 00:03:54,484
That's one way to do it.

58
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:56,278
Zanya Kisaragi, right?

59
00:03:56,278 --> 00:03:58,572
A ninja's got to do what
a ninja's got to do.

60
00:03:58,572 --> 00:04:00,490
(yells)

61
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:02,075
Right back
where I started.

62
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,660
(whimpers)

63
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:07,164
For the record, I don't plan on
using any of those hate cards.

64
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:09,416
My skills are enough
to beat you.

65
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,625
Hurry up, Akatsuki!

66
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:12,461
(laughing)

67
00:04:12,461 --> 00:04:14,463
Stop trying to
act so cool.

68
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:18,049
I remember when you used to run
around dressed like a ninja too.

69
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,259
Huh?

70
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,469
Read the sign,
it's over there.

71
00:04:20,469 --> 00:04:22,262
Thanks, I just hope
I can make it.

72
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:23,597
(whimpers)

73
00:04:23,597 --> 00:04:25,640
How do you
know about that?

74
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:28,769
Oh, don't tell
me you forgot.

75
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:30,562
The Kanahebi
style ninjas.

76
00:04:30,562 --> 00:04:33,398
The day they
were captured.

77
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:34,566
It can't be!

78
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,282
♪

79
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:44,576
The ninjas are now
being led out by police.

80
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:45,911
From what we're hearing,

81
00:04:45,911 --> 00:04:48,371
this completes the capture
of all Kanahebi style ninjas.

82
00:04:48,371 --> 00:04:51,333
♪

83
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:53,043
I don't think so.

84
00:04:53,043 --> 00:04:55,754
(grunting)

85
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:57,297
(shouts of confusion)

86
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:59,674
(coughing)

87
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:01,092
Stop them!

88
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:02,677
Don't let them escape!

89
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:06,389
♪

90
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:07,432
Father!

91
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:08,642
I don't understand.

92
00:05:08,642 --> 00:05:10,268
Why can't we let them go?

93
00:05:10,268 --> 00:05:12,020
Just this once.

94
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:14,356
They're way too awesome
to be locked up.

95
00:05:14,356 --> 00:05:17,400
My son, one day
you'll realize

96
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:20,278
it's my job to ensure
that justice is done.

97
00:05:20,278 --> 00:05:21,530
I'm sorry.

98
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:23,698
♪

99
00:05:23,698 --> 00:05:25,575
This isn't over.

100
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:29,162
I'll make sure our traditions
live on in spite of them.

101
00:05:29,162 --> 00:05:33,375
You will follow in my
footsteps, won't you, my son?

102
00:05:33,375 --> 00:05:40,048
♪

103
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:41,633
You're one of them.

104
00:05:41,633 --> 00:05:42,926
And you escaped.

105
00:05:42,926 --> 00:05:45,470
Head of the famous
Kanahebi family.

106
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:47,472
That's who
you're looking at.

107
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:51,184
The guy who's gonna demolish and
embarrass you in the next match.

108
00:05:51,184 --> 00:05:52,853
‐Huh?
‐Huh?

109
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:54,437
What a small world!

110
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:56,022
Katana, that is.

111
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:57,315
This is Paruko Nanana,

112
00:05:57,315 --> 00:05:59,985
live from the Chohakone
Mountains with breaking news!

113
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:01,945
The descendent
of a legendary ninja

114
00:06:01,945 --> 00:06:03,321
is a student
here at Sen‐Cad.

115
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:04,865
Let's go in
for a closer look.

116
00:06:04,865 --> 00:06:06,408
♪

117
00:06:06,408 --> 00:06:07,325
What can I say?

118
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:08,785
Ninjas have
always been cool.

119
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:11,454
Everyone wants to join 'em
cause nobody can beat 'em,

120
00:06:11,454 --> 00:06:13,164
and don't you forget it.

121
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:15,667
One unknown fact is that
up until a few years ago,

122
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:18,461
we were still being
asked to work as spies.

123
00:06:18,461 --> 00:06:21,006
The Kanahebi ninja was
a corrupt organization.

124
00:06:21,006 --> 00:06:22,507
Said to have hired
out their members

125
00:06:22,507 --> 00:06:24,551
to commit all
types of crimes.

126
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:25,844
No one's perfect.

127
00:06:25,844 --> 00:06:26,970
Remember, the ninja arts

128
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:29,014
have been passed down
over generations.

129
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:30,974
My dad always said
that it'd be a waste

130
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:33,101
if we didn't use our skills
to make a little coin.

131
00:06:33,101 --> 00:06:34,185
Know what I'm saying?

132
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:36,688
That is until the time
he got caught red‐handed

133
00:06:36,688 --> 00:06:40,525
by your old man, Police
Commissioner Kisaragi.

134
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:42,277
‐Hmm!
‐Hmm!

135
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:44,446
Did you hear that?

136
00:06:44,446 --> 00:06:46,031
It was enough of
a shocker to learn

137
00:06:46,031 --> 00:06:48,033
that we have a real,
live ninja in our midst,

138
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:50,076
but now it turns out that
he's also got a connection

139
00:06:50,076 --> 00:06:51,870
to Zanya's past.

140
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:52,871
Is this true?

141
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:54,539
Your father's really
the Police Commissioner?

142
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:55,790
Tell us about it.

143
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:57,667
Do you eat a lot of
doughnuts at your house?

144
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:58,835
(giggling)

145
00:06:58,835 --> 00:07:02,672
Let's get this
match started.

146
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:06,259
Striking down bandits
with skillful card play.

147
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,552
Luminize!

148
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:10,680
Behold, Great Oedo
Criminal Arrest Record.

149
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,556
Capture.

150
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:14,142
Constrict and
swallow 'em whole.

151
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:15,477
I luminize!

152
00:07:15,477 --> 00:07:17,896
Cobra Crow
Demonic Nightmare.

153
00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:19,564
What's going on?

154
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:21,441
Do I sense some
tension in the air?

155
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,652
I wonder if that Daddy drama
we just found out about

156
00:07:23,652 --> 00:07:27,530
has something
to do with it.

157
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:29,783
Ready, set.

158
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:31,993
Buddyfight!

159
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:35,038
‐Time to raise the flag!
‐Time to raise the flag!

160
00:07:35,038 --> 00:07:38,375
Katana World!

161
00:07:38,375 --> 00:07:40,502
I'm fighting for
Katana World too.

162
00:07:40,502 --> 00:07:42,879
♪

163
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:43,797
Here.

164
00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:45,090
I found it.

165
00:07:45,090 --> 00:07:46,257
Listen to this.

166
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:49,594
"Secret ninja organization,
Kanahebi style ninjas,

167
00:07:49,594 --> 00:07:51,221
rounded up and arrested."

168
00:07:51,221 --> 00:07:53,682
It says it was a really big
story when we were little.

169
00:07:53,682 --> 00:07:55,475
So this guy's serious?

170
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:57,936
He really is a descendent
of ninja warriors?

171
00:07:57,936 --> 00:08:00,647
Talk about being born to
do something, eh, bro?

172
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:02,482
I'm stoked to see
how his play style

173
00:08:02,482 --> 00:08:04,943
will mesh with
Zanya's strategy.

174
00:08:04,943 --> 00:08:06,111
I'm not worried.

175
00:08:06,111 --> 00:08:08,405
Big Z's the best Katana
World fighter there is.

176
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:09,698
You'll see!

177
00:08:09,698 --> 00:08:12,283
♪

178
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:15,495
Did you draw your secret
weapon: Lethal Formation?

179
00:08:15,495 --> 00:08:17,080
No biggie, go ahead.

180
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,331
Use it if you want.

181
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:19,791
You know my moves.

182
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:21,543
I guess I'll have to
shake things up a bit

