be using his signature move?

194
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:51,448
Is this some sort
of new strategy

195
00:08:51,448 --> 00:08:53,116
or is Zanya just
scrambling out there

196
00:08:53,116 --> 00:08:55,660
because his opponent's been
studying his fighting style?

197
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:58,621
Either way, we're in
for an exciting match.

198
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:01,291
Come on, Big Z.

199
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:03,293
I'm just giving
him a handicap.

200
00:09:03,293 --> 00:09:06,337
I call Stealth Ninja
Kirikakure Saizo to center!

201
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:11,301
♪

202
00:09:11,301 --> 00:09:13,011
End of move.

203
00:09:13,011 --> 00:09:15,180
Nice try, I guess.

204
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:16,765
But you still
don't measure up.

205
00:09:16,765 --> 00:09:18,141
Not against guys like me.

206
00:09:18,141 --> 00:09:19,517
We're the real deal.

207
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:22,645
♪

208
00:09:22,645 --> 00:09:26,107
Prepare to be schooled in
Kanahebi style ninjitsu.

209
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,692
Alright, draw.

210
00:09:27,692 --> 00:09:29,152
Charge and draw!

211
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:31,112
Ha!

212
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:33,948
Ninja Arts Final Showdown
on the Gojo Bridge,

213
00:09:33,948 --> 00:09:36,701
and my powerful
dark ninja technique:

214
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:39,037
Poison Mist
Formation.

215
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:41,289
I think both of
those are set spells.

216
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:42,665
The nerve!

217
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:45,919
This guy's taking a page
right out of Zanya's playbook.

218
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:49,214
I call to the right
Sky Ninja Yamigarasu.

