00:11:12,547 --> 00:11:17,051
♪

255
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,803
Call to the right,
Electron Ninja Shiden,

256
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:23,641
and on the left,
Stealth Ninja Kirikakure Saizo!

257
00:11:23,641 --> 00:11:26,269
Finally, I'll buddy
call Tsukikage!

258
00:11:26,269 --> 00:11:27,228
Nin.

259
00:11:27,228 --> 00:11:29,230
Zanya's called
out his ninjas too.

260
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:31,566
Time to stealth it up.

261
00:11:31,566 --> 00:11:34,402
First, I'll take
care of your buddy.

262
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:37,405
Tsukikage,
attack Yamigarasu!

263
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:38,406
Nin!

264
00:11:38,406 --> 00:11:42,994
♪

265
00:11:42,994 --> 00:11:44,829
(grunting)

266
00:11:44,829 --> 00:11:47,123
(laughs)

267
00:11:47,123 --> 00:11:50,627
Set spell, Final Showdown,
on the Great Gojo Bridge.

268
00:11:50,627 --> 00:11:52,503
And so the
fun begins, huh?

269
00:11:52,503 --> 00:11:55,506
Now, we're only able to
attack the center position.

270
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:57,842
So, then take out
the center Tsukikage.

271
00:11:57,842 --> 00:11:59,010
Attack!

272
00:11:59,010 --> 00:12:01,137
♪

273
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:03,389
Ability: Flame Barrier.

274
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:06,726
♪

275
00:12:06,726 --> 00:12:08,519
(grunting)

276
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:11,189
♪

277
00:12:11,189 --> 00:12:12,357
I don't get it!

278
00:12:12,357 --> 00:12:14,442
Why is Gokuen's
defense so strong?

279
00:12:14,442 --> 00:12:16,569
You don't know
about his ability?

280
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:19,447
All I do is discard
one ninja from my hand

281
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:22,116
and his defense is increased
for the rest of the turn.

282
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:28,206
You could try attacking
the left or right instead,

283
00:12:28,206 --> 00:12:32,043
but you aware of Yoichi and
Yamigarasu's abilities right?

284
00:12:32,043 --> 00:12:34,879
When a monster directly
opposing them moves,

285
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:38,549
they get to inflict direct
damage to the opposing fighter.

286
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:39,676
That's right.

287
00:12:39,676 --> 00:12:41,636
It's an ability, so
it doesn't really matter

288
00:12:41,636 --> 00:12:43,346
whether the Great
Gojo Bridge is there

289
00:12:43,346 --> 00:12:45,139
and the center
is blocked or not.

290
00:12:45,139 --> 00:12:47,308
I'll inflict damage
on you either way,

291
00:12:47,308 --> 00:12:49,185
little doughnut eater.

292
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:52,397
Being able to cause damage
no matter what he does?

293
00:12:52,397 --> 00:12:54,357
It sounds a lot
like my ability.

294
00:12:54,357 --> 00:12:56,651
And you're a special rare,
so that's saying something,

295
00:12:56,651 --> 00:12:59,570
but knowing Zanya,
he'll find a way out of this.

296
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:02,156
Even using Shiden and Saizo
to hit him with a link attack

297
00:13:02,156 --> 00:13:05,368
won't be enough to
defeat Gokuen in the center.

298
00:13:05,368 --> 00:13:07,787
So, there's no point
in attacking now.

299
00:13:07,787 --> 00:13:09,622
I declare
End of Move.

300
00:13:09,622 --> 00:13:10,790
That's perfect.

301
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,417
Ninja Art
Snake Gaze!

302
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:13,418
No way!

303
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:15,545
He cast a counter spell
without being attacked!

304
00:13:15,545 --> 00:13:25,430
♪

305
00:13:25,430 --> 00:13:27,015
That's what
I'm talking about!

306
00:13:27,015 --> 00:13:29,934
I'm gonna light
you up, Kisaragi!

307
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:31,311
(grunts)

308
00:13:31,311 --> 00:13:33,104
End of move.

309
00:13:33,104 --> 00:13:34,647
Hey, I don't get it!

310
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:36,482
Why'd Saizo
move like that?

311
00:13:36,482 --> 00:13:38,026
Snake Gaze is a
handy ninja art

312
00:13:38,026 --> 00:13:41,446
that forces one of the
opponent's monsters into action.

313
00:13:41,446 --> 00:13:44,449
Basically, Saizo had
no choice but to move,

314
00:13:44,449 --> 00:13:48,244
and activate
Yamigarasu's ability.

315
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:50,413
Your attacks are
too weak to reach me.

316
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:52,206
♪

317
00:13:52,206 --> 00:13:54,333
Now you're realizing that
as the match wears on,

318
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:57,003
you're slowly receiving
more and more damage.

319
00:13:57,003 --> 00:13:58,838
This is how the
ninjas, you've idolized

320
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,965
since you were a
kid, actually fight.

321
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:04,802
♪

322
00:14:04,802 --> 00:14:06,763
It was that day
that I stopped dreaming

323
00:14:06,763 --> 00:14:08,431
of becoming
one of them.

324
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:10,475
It would have
been impossible.

325
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:12,560
(rain falling)

326
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:21,778
♪

327
00:14:21,778 --> 00:14:22,945
(laughing)

328
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:23,988
Spare me.

329
00:14:23,988 --> 00:14:26,324
You and I both know that
for fighters like us,

330
00:14:26,324 --> 00:14:27,950
dreams are pointless.

331
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,827
It's better to
live in reality.

332
00:14:29,827 --> 00:14:32,830
I serve Rouga now
and follow his orders.

333
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:35,124
Now, prepare
for my next wave.

334
00:14:35,124 --> 00:14:37,585
Activate set spell:
Poison Mist Formation!

335
00:14:37,585 --> 00:14:41,005
♪

336
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:43,841
(grunts)

337
00:14:43,841 --> 00:14:45,134
Not too shabby, huh?

338
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:47,804
It inflicts damage on you
every time it's my turn.

339
00:14:47,804 --> 00:14:50,807
It may not look like
much, but it works.

340
00:14:50,807 --> 00:14:52,767
I totally get
what's going on.

341
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,227
So fill me in, man!

342
00:14:54,227 --> 00:14:56,646
Kanahebi's got a pretty
unique fighting style.

343
00:14:56,646 --> 00:14:58,773
He's not the type
who'd use an impact card

344
00:14:58,773 --> 00:15:01,818
or equip an item and
attack an opponent himself.

345
00:15:01,818 --> 00:15:03,194
Being a fan of
ninja warfare,

346
00:15:03,194 --> 00:15:05,613
Zanya predicted how
Kanahebi'd play it.

347
00:15:05,613 --> 00:15:08,324
That's why he ditched
the Lethal Formation.

348
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:10,326
You want to explain
that in English, yo?

349
00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:12,453
It's all about
the activation.

350
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:13,704
Lethal Formation's triggered

351
00:15:13,704 --> 00:15:17,875
when an opponent uses an
impact, item or spell card.

352
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:20,670
But since Kanahebi doesn't
even use two of these,

353
00:15:20,670 --> 00:15:22,421
playing it
would be a waste.

354
00:15:22,421 --> 00:15:23,631
That leaves
Star Crusher.

355
00:15:23,631 --> 00:15:26,092
That's activated by
spells and Moon Fang,

356
00:15:26,092 --> 00:15:28,386
that's activated
by an impact card.

357
00:15:28,386 --> 00:15:29,554
It makes sense.

358
00:15:29,554 --> 00:15:31,722
The three choices
wouldn't come into play,

359
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:33,224
so it wouldn't
even be a trap.

360
00:15:33,224 --> 00:15:35,101
Man, you got to
hand it to Zanya.

361
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:37,687
He's always one
step ahead, isn't he?

362
00:15:37,687 --> 00:15:39,188
I'm still kinda lost.

363
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:40,898
Go over it again
from the top.

364
00:15:40,898 --> 00:15:42,233
Oh, Drum.

365
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:45,069
You armor dragons never
have been too quick.

366
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:46,571
Come on, Z!

367
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:50,908
♪

368
00:15:50,908 --> 00:15:52,994
Clear a path
to the center!

369
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:54,412
Take out his buddy!

370
00:15:54,412 --> 00:15:58,249
♪

371
00:15:58,249 --> 00:16:00,710
Ability: Nanomachine
Body Replacement.

372
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:02,420
♪

373
00:16:02,420 --> 00:16:04,088
Nin.

374
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:05,256
(growls)

375
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:07,216
I'll soon take
care of that.

376
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:09,760
Yamigarasu!

377
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,387
Nanomachine
Body Replacement.

378
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:13,848
♪

379
00:16:13,848 --> 00:16:14,932
Nin.

380
00:16:14,932 --> 00:16:16,851
Gokuen.

381
00:16:16,851 --> 00:16:18,311
Nanomachine
Body Replacement.

382
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:19,979
♪

383
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:22,732
(grunting)

384
00:16:22,732 --> 00:16:24,442
‐Nin.
‐Ha!

385
00:16:24,442 --> 00:16:26,736
You just wasted
three cards from your hand

386
00:16:26,736 --> 00:16:30,948
cause you're so desperate
to protect your center.

387
00:16:30,948 --> 00:16:31,824
He's right.

388
00:16:31,824 --> 00:16:33,117
That's a lot
of cards to lose.

389
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:35,244
Look closely, Kazane.

390
00:16:35,244 --> 00:16:37,455
The three cards he used
for the Body Replacement

391
00:16:37,455 --> 00:16:40,708
were Back Hand, Right Hand
and Lethal Formation.

392
00:16:40,708 --> 00:16:42,460
Each of which are
ineffective cards

393
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:44,212
against the ninja's
fighting style.

394
00:16:44,212 --> 00:16:47,298
That's why Zanya
sacrificed them.

395
00:16:47,298 --> 00:16:50,301
Man, he really knows how
to work with what he's got.

396
00:16:50,301 --> 00:16:54,597
♪

397
00:16:54,597 --> 00:16:55,806
(growls)

398
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:59,060
At this rate, the match is going
to take all day to finish.

399
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:01,979
They're averaging only
one damage point a turn.

400
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:04,440
Even so, if the battle
continues this way,

401
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:08,986
Zanya's sure to lose it.

402
00:17:08,986 --> 00:17:12,490
Tsukikage, Shiden,
time for a link attack!

403
00:17:12,490 --> 00:17:14,617
Nin!

404
00:17:14,617 --> 00:17:17,870
Destructo Blade!

405
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,497
Get him!

406
00:17:24,168 --> 00:17:25,503
Better watch out.

407
00:17:25,503 --> 00:17:28,339
If your monsters on the
left or right move...

408
00:17:28,339 --> 00:17:29,423
We warned him.

409
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:32,134
Now, we zap him.

410
00:17:32,134 --> 00:17:34,720
(grunts)

411
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:37,014
End of move.

412
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:39,016
You're strong just
like I knew you'd be,

413
00:17:39,016 --> 00:17:41,352
but so am I, and
we're still in this.

414
00:17:41,352 --> 00:17:42,562
Come on, Tsukikage!

415
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:44,146
Let's put our
plan into action!

416
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:46,357
♪

417
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:48,276
Not if I have
something to say.

418
00:17:48,276 --> 00:17:49,694
♪

419
00:17:49,694 --> 00:17:52,446
Bait set spell!

420
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:54,031
(grunts)

421
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:56,993
Call to the center,
Sniping Ninja Yoichi!

422
00:17:56,993 --> 00:17:59,287
♪

423
00:17:59,287 --> 00:18:02,123
Now, Yoichi on the
left attack Tsukikage!

424
00:18:02,123 --> 00:18:06,502
♪

425
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:11,048
Ability: Nanomachine
Body Replacement.

426
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:12,258
Nin.

427
00:18:12,258 --> 00:18:14,385
Yamigarasu,
hit him again.

428
00:18:14,385 --> 00:18:20,850
♪

429
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:22,643
Sorry, Tsukikage,
forgive me.

430
00:18:26,647 --> 00:18:30,610
Looks like you're finally
out of cards to sacrifice.

431
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:33,404
You know what's up when
it comes to the ninja arts.

432
00:18:33,404 --> 00:18:34,739
Huh?

433
00:18:34,739 --> 00:18:36,365
But something
confuses me.

434
00:18:36,365 --> 00:18:40,620
With skills like yours, why
are you serving Rouga Aragami?

435
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:44,498
My guess is that you dream
of starting a revival.

436
00:18:46,292 --> 00:18:49,670
Like I said before,
dreams are a waste of time.

437
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:51,213
♪

438
00:18:51,213 --> 00:18:53,966
This legacy was left
to me and me alone,

439
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:58,220
but I realized it's useless
against true strength.

440
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:00,598
Aragami is a
powerful fighter.

441
00:19:00,598 --> 00:19:03,100
He's on a totally
different level than us.

442
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:05,186
So, I decided the best
thing for me to do

443
00:19:05,186 --> 00:19:06,354
is just follow his lead

444
00:19:06,354 --> 00:19:09,774
and maybe learn a
few tricks along the way.

445
00:19:09,774 --> 00:19:13,653
Plus, I get a lot of time
to chill and have fun.

446
00:19:13,653 --> 00:19:16,113
(snickering)

447
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:18,115
Makes sense, that's
what I thought.

448
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:20,993
If that's true, then
you and I are the same.

449
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:23,287
No, cause I
stopped running away!

450
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:25,289
You're still doing it.

451
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:26,499
Huh?

452
00:19:26,499 --> 00:19:30,586
Draw, charge, and draw!

453
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:31,837
Huh?

454
00:19:31,837 --> 00:19:32,880
I think he got it.

455
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:34,298
Got get him, Zanya!

456
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:38,094
Now, I call Leaping Ninja
Sarutobi to the center!

457
00:19:39,512 --> 00:19:41,055
Let's show him!

458
00:19:41,055 --> 00:19:43,766
Okay, Vertical
Straight Line right!

459
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:45,476
(grunts)

460
00:19:45,476 --> 00:19:48,479
Sarutobi has the unusual
ability to enter the drop zone

461
00:19:48,479 --> 00:19:51,065
and take an opponent's
spell card with them!

462
00:19:51,065 --> 00:19:53,359
Now you see it,
now you don't!

463
00:19:53,359 --> 00:19:56,654
Gojo Bridge is falling down,
falling down!

464
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:00,074
Not good!

465
00:20:00,074 --> 00:20:02,243
Now listen to me.

466
00:20:02,243 --> 00:20:04,954
I had to put my
dream on hold.

467
00:20:04,954 --> 00:20:08,207
My dream lives here in
the world of Buddyfight.

468
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:12,294
By using Katana World,
I get to channel it.

469
00:20:12,294 --> 00:20:14,130
Is that why?

470
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:16,757
And one day, Tsukikage
and I will join the ranks

471
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:18,300
of the Buddy Police

472
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:21,887
and become stealth
masters of justice!

473
00:20:21,887 --> 00:20:24,223
Every time I give
my all in a match,

474
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:26,642
it's to achieve
that future!

475
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:28,269
Be quick!

476
00:20:28,269 --> 00:20:30,229
Five Heavenly Swords,
Onimaru!

477
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,856
♪

478
00:20:31,856 --> 00:20:33,524
I thought you
would know better.

479
00:20:33,524 --> 00:20:35,735
Dreams like that
aren't worth anything.

480
00:20:35,735 --> 00:20:37,570
♪

481
00:20:37,570 --> 00:20:39,363
Replacing Shiden
and Saizo.

482
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:42,199
I call to the left position,
Wanderer, the Gold.

483
00:20:42,199 --> 00:20:46,746
♪

484
00:20:46,746 --> 00:20:49,874
In bloom all year,
a cherry blossom storm.

485
00:20:49,874 --> 00:20:53,377
Scatter their petal powers and
seize control of this match!

486
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:55,588
Oh, no, not The Gold!

487
00:20:55,588 --> 00:20:58,549
He can attack all your
monsters at the same time.

488
00:20:58,549 --> 00:21:00,134
The sweet smell
of victory.

489
00:21:00,134 --> 00:21:02,887
Cherry Blossom Storm!

490
00:21:02,887 --> 00:21:06,390
Huh?

491
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:07,767
(grunting)

492
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:12,521
♪

493
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:16,317
Don't you know what a privilege
it is to have a buddy?

494
00:21:16,317 --> 00:21:17,568
With your buddy
at your side,

495
00:21:17,568 --> 00:21:20,029
you can achieve anything
you set your mind to.

496
00:21:20,029 --> 00:21:22,490
Even if the odds
are against you.

497
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:26,202
So why are you letting
Rouga tell you what to do?

498
00:21:26,202 --> 00:21:27,745
I don't know.

499
00:21:27,745 --> 00:21:29,622
You have a point.

500
00:21:29,622 --> 00:21:31,624
Huh?

501
00:21:31,624 --> 00:21:34,752
♪

502
00:21:34,752 --> 00:21:37,129
Remote Punishment!

503
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:42,426
The thing
about Gold

504
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:43,928
is that he gives
one damage point

505
00:21:43,928 --> 00:21:45,346
for each monster
he defeats.

506
00:21:45,346 --> 00:21:47,431
He's down to just
three life points.

507
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:49,225
Can he do it?

508
00:21:49,225 --> 00:21:51,936
I'll defeat the ninja
I once idolized!

509
00:21:51,936 --> 00:21:54,063
I've never seen Zanya
like this before.

510
00:21:54,063 --> 00:21:56,732
You should see him when
he wakes up in the morning.

511
00:21:56,732 --> 00:21:58,234
I've been waiting
for this day

512
00:21:58,234 --> 00:22:02,279
for as long as
I can remember!

513
00:22:02,279 --> 00:22:04,448
Five Heavenly Swords,
Onimaru!

514
00:22:04,448 --> 00:22:06,659
Twisted Spirit
Purification!

515
00:22:06,659 --> 00:22:11,205
♪

516
00:22:11,205 --> 00:22:12,414
Game over.

517
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:15,376
Winner: Zanya Kisaragi.

518
00:22:15,376 --> 00:22:18,712
Impressive display, but
the defeat sets us back.

519
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:20,297
Who will fight next?

520
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:22,508
I will.

521
00:22:22,508 --> 00:22:24,218
No, I'll go.

522
00:22:24,218 --> 00:22:25,678
Huh?

523
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:35,521
♪

524
00:22:35,521 --> 00:22:37,481
What do you think?

525
00:22:37,481 --> 00:22:39,066
Follow the dream?

526
00:22:39,066 --> 00:22:46,031
♪

527
00:22:49,326 --> 00:22:50,494
It's time for...

528
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:51,620
Tasuku and Gao's...

529
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:53,914
‐Card of the day!
‐Card of the day!

530
00:22:53,914 --> 00:22:57,167
Today's card is called
